summary: Email chain between Telegraph journalist Josie Ensor and US Attorney's Office (likely Southern District of New York) regarding an unredacted witness name in a Ghislaine Maxwell court filing. The journalist inquires if they can report the name, and prosecutors urgently request not to publish while they verify.

persons.name: Josie Ensor

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Subject of the criminal case referenced; the inquiry concerns a filing in United States vs. Maxwell where a witness name was allegedly left unredacted.

connections.description: Ensor is a journalist inquiring about a procedural matter in Maxwell's criminal case.

events.title: Journalist inquiry about unredacted witness name
events.description: Telegraph journalist Josie Ensor emails the US Attorney's Office to ask if they can report the name of a government witness that was left unredacted in a recent Ghislaine Maxwell court filing (Document #453).

keyFacts: A recent filing in United States vs. Ghislaine Maxwell (Document #453) allegedly contained an unredacted name of one of the government's proposed witnesses.
The judge had allowed witnesses and victims to remain anonymous through the trial if they chose.
The defense was responsible for the filing where the name was left unredacted.
The US Attorney's Office was urgently checking the accuracy of the journalist's claim and requested the name not be published in the meantime.
